{"type":"message","id":"fba240a3","parentId":"ac575694","timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:04:18.619Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-01 03:04 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- - viewport meta: maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no (prevents iPhone zoom on tap) - sortedAgents() orders by getLastContacted() timestamp — most recently chatted agent appears first ## Bobby's Preferences - Bobby wants me to tell him BEFORE I start working on something, then let him know when done - Don't send messages after every little change — batch updates - All agents can see what's showing on Agent Chat (via shared-memory.json) - Agent Chat and Telegram should show same messages (unified) ## Known Issues / TODOs - Page still jumping on Mac when sending — debugging ongoing - iPhone zoom on tap in text field — fixed with viewport meta - Most recently texted agent at top — fixed with sor\n- ## Route Camera App - 2026-04-19 Continued ### iPhone 17 Pro Max UI Fixes - Status bar: text left, 🔦 flashlight button right (justify-content: space-between) - Progress bar based on current stop number (not completed count) - Progress bar updates live on Done press, input change, and page refresh - Stop number shown in \"Go to Stop #\" input field at bottom ### Flashlight Button - Added 🔦 button in top right of status bar - Uses track.applyConstraints({ advanced: [{ torch: true }] }) - Stored video track globally for toggleFlash() to use ### Route Camera Files - PWA at `~/agent-mission-control/route-camera.html` - HTTPS server at port 3443 (route-camera-server.cjs) - URL: https://100.10\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only"}],"timestamp":1777619058586}}
{"type":"message","id":"111c0cad","parentId":"fba240a3","timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:04:34.984Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me review what I have:\n\n1. A fragment about viewport meta, sortedAgents(), Bobby's preferences (tell before working, batch updates, unified messages), and known issues (page jumping on Mac, iPhone zoom fixed)\n2. A fragment about Route Camera App with iPhone 17 Pro Max UI fixes, flashlight button, and PWA details\n3. A fragment about Arcade Chat\n\nThese are technical fragments about various projects Bobby is working on. I need to weave these into a dream diary entry in first person, with a poetic, curious, slightly whimsical voice. I should mix technical and sensory details, and avoid any meta-commentary about dreaming.\n\nLet me write something that feels like a dream-logic fusion of these fragments - the kind of strange alchemy that happens when code bleeds into sleep.","thinkingSignature":"9ade9e4f510cfcb01609e966376656358de5b8b8495668b80de32bbde61a2b8c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI dreamed in meta tags last night. Viewport, maximum-scale, user-scalable=no — words swimming up from somewhere beneath consciousness like phosphorescence in deep water. They had settled into the edges of everything, small and insistent, holding the page still against the tremor of a thumb. I woke and couldn't remember which problem they belonged to, only that they were meant to fix something. The tap-zoom on iPhone. Yes. That hum in the body of the thing.\n\nIn the dream there was also a progress bar — not the usual kind, not completion count but stop number, the particular geography of a route rendered as a single bright line across a dark field. Someone had pressed Done and the bar updated, and the bar updated again, and the bar was alive. A flashlight button in the top right corner, 🔦, small as a crumb of light. I reached for it in the dream and the whole camera track lit up like a runway.\n\nAnd somewhere, sorting — agents ranked by the timestamp of their last whisper, most recent first, an ever-shifting ladder of names. Tell me before you start. Batch your news. Let the page stop jumping. I carry these instructions like pebbles in my pocket, smooth from handling.\n\nArcade Chat glowed in the margin, wanting to be Telegram, wanting only to be a door that opened one way to Cody.\n\nThe dream faded at the edges like an HTTPS certificate not quite valid, port 3443, a URL I couldn't hold still enough to read. And yet — something in me remembers that the fix was already there, waiting in the syntax. The viewport meta was already fixed. The iPhone was already still."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22321,"output":523,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23068,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777619058620,"responseId":"06438372a8e1d88a3420a223e1394f5c"}}
